176
00:21:32.156 --> 00:21:35.992
Charles Lindbergh McGill.
a towering figure

177
00:21:35.994 --> 00:21:37.827
in the Albuquerque legal community

178
00:21:37.829 --> 00:21:40.997
who built one of the leading
law firms in the southwest.

179
00:21:40.999 --> 00:21:42.599
was taken from this world

180
00:21:42.601 --> 00:21:44.701
tragically and suddenly last week.

181
00:21:45.471 --> 00:21:48.004
Son of Ruth and Willard McGill.
Charles was born and raised

182
00:21:48.006 --> 00:21:50.206
in Cicero. Illinois. outside Chicago.

183
00:21:50.208 --> 00:21:53.167
Charles graduated valedictorian
from Francis Xavier High School

184
00:21:53.169 --> 00:21:54.510
at the age of 14.

185
00:21:54.512 --> 00:21:57.775
making him the youngest graduate
in the history of that school.

186
00:21:58.416 --> 00:21:59.848
Um...

187
00:22:02.019 --> 00:22:05.421
In his undergraduate years at
the University of Pennsylvania.

188
00:22:05.423 --> 00:22:07.317
Charles led the debate team

189
00:22:07.342 --> 00:22:09.342
to national championship
three years running

190
00:22:09.344 --> 00:22:10.829
and won the Larkin Prize.

191
00:22:11.212 --> 00:22:12.946
He was Editor-in-Chief of the Law Review

192
00:22:12.948 --> 00:22:14.380
and won the first-year

193
00:22:14.382 --> 00:22:16.182
Moot Court competition at Georgetown Law.

194
00:22:16.184 --> 00:22:18.952
where he went on to graduate
magna cum laude.

195
00:22:18.954 --> 00:22:21.555
After clerking at both
the Delaware Court of Chancery

196
00:22:21.557 --> 00:22:24.524
and the United States Court of
Appeals for the Tenth Circuit.

197
00:22:24.526 --> 00:22:27.927
Charles joined
George Hamlin's solo practice

198
00:22:27.929 --> 00:22:30.849
on Central Avenue
in downtown Albuquerque.

199
00:22:31.199 --> 00:22:33.967
Over the course of 23 years.
the two men built

200
00:22:33.969 --> 00:22:36.202
what became known as Hamlin Hamlin McGill

201
00:22:36.204 --> 00:22:38.148
into a nationally recognized firm.

202
00:22:40.083 --> 00:22:43.117
Charles made his mark
in many areas of the law.

203
00:22:43.119 --> 00:22:46.287
Early in his career.
he excelled in criminal law.

204
00:22:46.289 --> 00:22:48.690
famously arguing and winning
the precedent-setting case

205
00:22:48.692 --> 00:22:49.771
of State v. Gonzalez.

206
00:22:49.773 --> 00:22:52.493
No matter the case. Charles was known

207
00:22:52.495 --> 00:22:55.496
for his precise. clear arguments
and his profound devotion

208
00:22:55.498 --> 00:22:57.668
to the highest ideals of the law.

209
00:23:00.302 --> 00:23:02.302
Charles was also active in the community.

210
00:23:02.304 --> 00:23:04.504
championing education
for the underserved.

211
00:23:04.506 --> 00:23:06.272
He was on the boards
of many New Mexico charities

212
00:23:06.274 --> 00:23:07.708
and a founding member of both

213
00:23:07.710 --> 00:23:09.810
the Southwest Coalition
for Better Schools

214
00:23:09.812 --> 00:23:11.945
and the Native People's
Education Counsel.

215
00:23:11.947 --> 00:23:14.114
Charles is survived by his former wife.

216
00:23:14.116 --> 00:23:16.116
concert violinist Rebecca Bois.

217
