275
00:35:30.017 --> 00:35:32.517
You want to pick up 2?

276
00:35:37.965 --> 00:35:40.555
I'll go ahead and take the copy for you.

277
00:35:59.590 --> 00:36:00.924
Bruce had the speed.

278
00:36:00.924 --> 00:36:02.801
He could kick you
before you saw him move.

279
00:36:02.801 --> 00:36:04.668
You ever watched the Liston fight?

280
00:36:04.670 --> 00:36:06.805
All right. we're talking
about what? Boxing?

281
00:36:06.805 --> 00:36:07.826
'Cause that's something else.

282
00:36:07.851 --> 00:36:09.575
No. we're talking about a street fight.

283
00:36:09.600 --> 00:36:10.809
Street fight?

284
00:36:10.809 --> 00:36:12.208
Great. So. Bruce can kick.

285
00:36:12.210 --> 00:36:13.912
No. we're not talking about
a movie fight.

286
00:36:13.937 --> 00:36:15.202
We're talking about weight.

287
00:36:15.204 --> 00:36:16.356
We're talking about reach.

288
00:36:16.356 --> 00:36:17.621
Boxing is a sport.

289
00:36:17.623 --> 00:36:19.790
Martial arts is life and death.

290
00:36:19.792 --> 00:36:22.054
Look. I don't care how fast you are.

291
00:36:22.056 --> 00:36:23.841
Muhammad Ali hits you. you're going down.

292
00:36:23.843 --> 00:36:27.165
- That's a fact.
- Oh. if he hits you.

293
00:36:27.167 --> 00:36:30.721
Bruce Lee... he knows the anatomy.

294
00:36:30.746 --> 00:36:31.830
He's got the moves.

295
00:36:31.830 --> 00:36:32.998
He's gonna find an opening.

296
00:36:32.998 --> 00:36:35.364
Without power. the...
the opening doesn't mean squat.

297
00:36:35.469 --> 00:36:36.768
How much does he weigh?

298
00:36:36.793 --> 00:36:38.712
I don't know. Maybe a buck-30.

299
00:36:38.712 --> 00:36:40.949
Ali was the heavyweight champ.

300
00:36:41.089 --> 00:36:43.008
He's got at least 100 pounds on Lee.

301
00:36:43.008 --> 00:36:45.741
Bruce feints for Ali's head.
but he goes low

302
00:36:45.743 --> 00:36:47.321
and he sweeps him to the deck.

303
00:36:47.346 --> 00:36:48.678
Ali goes down hard.

304
00:36:48.680 --> 00:36:50.547
It's all over.

305
00:36:50.549 --> 00:36:53.416
- Does he have a gun?
- I'm sorry?

306
00:36:53.418 --> 00:36:55.604
Does Bruce Lee have a gun?

307
00:36:55.604 --> 00:36:56.937
Because if he doesn't.

308
00:36:56.939 --> 00:36:58.873
it's Ali in three minutes or less.

309
00:36:59.299 --> 00:37:01.465
See? That's what I'm saying.

310
00:37:01.467 --> 00:37:02.866
That's what I'm s...

311
00:37:02.868 --> 00:37:05.305
Hey. hold on. Wait. Wait.

312
00:37:08.040 --> 00:37:10.644
Did you sign. uh. Tina's birthday card?

313
00:37:11.061 --> 00:37:13.397
- No.
- Would you mind?

314
00:37:14.198 --> 00:37:15.858
Not at all.

315
00:37:20.986 --> 00:37:23.005
You're way out of line on this.
I'm telling you.

316
00:37:23.007 --> 00:37:26.708
All I'm saying is. if Lee tried
to sweep Ali's legs.

317
00:37:26.710 --> 00:37:28.010
he'll just sidestep.

318
00:37:28.012 --> 00:37:30.864
Ali was fast for his size. yes.

319
00:37:30.889 --> 00:37:32.474
but if he gets hit with a low kick.

320
00:37:32.474 --> 00:37:33.809
he's not gonna know what to do.

321
00:37:33.809 --> 00:37:36.044
Oh. I know what he'll do.
He'll do just fine.

322
00:37:36.046 --> 00:37:37.445
You're nuts.

323
00:37:37.447 --> 00:37:38.981
- Thanks.
- Yep.

324
00:37:38.981 --> 00:37:41.291
Look. Bruce was a brawler. okay?

325
00:37:41.316 --> 00:37:42.549
He gets in quick...

326
00:40:03.254 --> 00:40:05.254
Uh. yeah?

327
00:40:05.827 --> 00:40:07.256
Ramirez.

328
00:40:07.258 --> 00:40:09.258
- Team leader.
- Yes. sir.

329
00:40:09.260 --> 00:40:11.994
So. Ramirez.
what do you think you're up to?

330
00:40:11.996 --> 00:40:13.795
We're just filling an order.

331
00:40:13.797 --> 00:40:15.303
Something wrong?

332
00:40:15.303 --> 00:40:18.438
May I ask why none of your guys
are wearing a lift belt?

333
00:40:19.374 --> 00:40:20.585
Lift belt.

334
00:40:21.167 --> 00:40:22.587
Oh. we... we don't usually...

335
00:40:22.589 --> 00:40:24.938
Stop what you're doing.
You go to the equipment room.

336
00:40:24.938 --> 00:40:26.798
You get lift belts and gloves.

337
00:40:27.106 --> 00:40:28.372
You use them.

338
00:40:28.374 --> 00:40:30.608
Rules are rules. Got me?

339
00:40:30.610 --> 00:40:32.376
Sure. Sure. Okay.

340
00:40:32.378 --> 00:40:33.639
On the double.

341
00:40:34.013 --> 00:40:35.778
Hey. hold up!

342
00:40:35.780 --> 00:40:37.311
Shut it down.

343
00:40:37.313 --> 00:40:38.583
Shut it down!

344
00:40:59.372 --> 00:41:01.372
Uh. excuse me.

345
00:41:01.374 --> 00:41:03.740
I think this belongs to you.

346
00:41:04.776 --> 00:41:06.442
Oh. my God.

347
00:41:08.046 --> 00:41:09.579
Thank you.

348
00:41:09.581 --> 00:41:11.047
Where did you find it?

349
00:41:11.385 --> 00:41:13.819
I need to talk to your manager.

350
00:41:14.889 --> 00:41:18.033
I waltz through security
with someone else's I.D.

351
00:41:18.033 --> 00:41:20.333
Nobody gives me a second look.

352
00:41:20.335 --> 00:41:22.496
When the rightful owner shows up.

353
00:41:22.496 --> 00:41:25.163
there's no facility-wide badge check.

354
00:41:25.165 --> 00:41:28.433
I find access doors
left unlocked or propped open.

355
00:41:28.435 --> 00:41:30.601
passwords written on Post-it notes.

356
00:41:30.603 --> 00:41:33.070
Warehouse workers are using pen and paper

357
00:41:33.072 --> 00:41:35.473
instead of electronic inventory devices.

358
00:41:35.475 --> 00:41:37.803
which leaves you wide open to pilfering.

359
00:41:37.803 --> 00:41:40.336
You got duplicate
routing numbers on cargo.

360
00:41:40.338 --> 00:41:42.405
surveillance-camera blind spots

361
00:41:42.407 --> 00:41:45.141
on the north
and the east side of the floor.

362
00:41:45.143 --> 00:41:48.144
inventory documents
that are going into the trash

363
00:41:48.146 --> 00:41:50.546
instead of being shredded. not to mention

364
00:41:50.548 --> 00:41:54.775
loading equipment being driven
at unsafe speeds and crews...

365
00:41:54.800 --> 00:41:56.933
- Wait. Wait.
- ...disregarding safe...

366
00:41:56.935 --> 00:41:58.116
Wait. Hold on. Hold on.

367
00:41:58.116 --> 00:41:59.682
Who are you. exactly?

368
00:41:59.684 --> 00:42:01.283
Ehrmantraut.

369
00:42:01.639 --> 00:42:03.458
Security consultant.

370
00:42:05.080 --> 00:42:06.164
All due respect.

371
00:42:06.164 --> 00:42:08.464
I don't know anything about
a security consultant.

372
00:42:08.466 --> 00:42:10.026
Well. you wouldn't. would you?

373
00:42:11.016 --> 00:42:13.259
Maybe you best call corporate.

374
00:42:13.739 --> 00:42:17.159
Try Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

375
00:42:35.926 --> 00:42:38.026
Truly sorry. Jimmy.

376
00:42:38.028 --> 00:42:40.662
Thank you. Cliff. Appreciate that.

377
00:42:43.166 --> 00:42:46.034
Hey. He was a hell of a lawyer.

378
00:42:46.036 --> 00:42:47.669
Yes. he was.

379
00:42:50.173 --> 00:42:51.684
Jimmy...

380
00:42:52.275 --> 00:42:54.842
we're going to miss him so much.

381
00:42:54.844 --> 00:42:57.011
Thank you. Brenda.

382
00:42:59.015 --> 00:43:01.382
I'm sorry for your loss.

383
00:43:01.384 --> 00:43:02.783
Thanks. Brian.

384
00:43:05.788 --> 00:43:08.456
Jimmy. I'm so sorry.

385
00:43:08.458 --> 00:43:11.158
Oh. Well. thanks. Appreciate that.

386
00:44:16.523 --> 00:44:19.480
I-I think I owe you
the truth about Chuck.

387
00:44:20.982 --> 00:44:22.727
Those lanterns.

388
00:44:24.360 --> 00:44:26.531
He was living in that house
without electricity

389
00:44:26.533 --> 00:44:28.133
for the better part of two years.

390
00:44:28.135 --> 00:44:30.401
He knew how to use those lanterns.

391
00:44:30.403 --> 00:44:32.137
He was careful. I saw it.

392
00:44:32.139 --> 00:44:33.538
I know you did. too.

393
00:44:33.540 --> 00:44:35.246
There was never a problem.

394
00:44:37.144 --> 00:44:39.577
I know it's a terrible thing to...

395
00:44:42.749 --> 00:44:45.616
I don't think what happened
was an accident.

396
00:44:55.495 --> 00:44:59.979
You probably heard
Chuck was retiring from HHM.

397
00:45:00.966 --> 00:45:02.940
But that's not the truth.

398
00:45:04.442 --> 00:45:08.821
The truth is
that we had a disagreement...

399
00:45:09.175 --> 00:45:11.073
and I pushed him out.

400
00:45:11.411 --> 00:45:12.677
I made him go.

401
00:45:12.679 --> 00:45:14.978
Chuck was sick for years.

402
00:45:14.980 --> 00:45:16.447
And after the bar hearing...

403
00:45:16.449 --> 00:45:18.115
The bar hearing
had nothing to do with it.

404
00:45:19.582 --> 00:45:21.036
Okay.

405
00:45:21.037 --> 00:45:23.878
The fact is. he started
getting better after that.

406
00:45:25.254 --> 00:45:26.506
He took more of an interest in the firm.

407
00:45:26.508 --> 00:45:29.509
He came to work.
We could leave the lights on.

408
00:45:29.511 --> 00:45:32.145
He was improving until
the thing with the insurance.

409
00:45:32.147 --> 00:45:34.581
So. I-it wasn't the bar hearing.

410
00:45:35.651 --> 00:45:37.683
The insurance...?

411
00:45:38.153 --> 00:45:40.686
It was a ridiculous thing.

412
00:45:42.524 --> 00:45:44.524
I should've just let it go.

413
00:45:44.526 --> 00:45:47.160
I mean. God knows
he's done enough for me.

414
00:45:47.610 --> 00:45:48.728
But he kept pushing.

415
00:45:48.730 --> 00:45:52.782
And I. um... I got my back up.

416
00:45:53.783 --> 00:45:55.535
What about the insurance?

417
00:45:55.537 --> 00:45:58.749
It was. uh. our malpractice insurance.

418
00:45:58.751 --> 00:46:00.276
They found out about Chuck's condition.

419
00:46:00.278 --> 00:46:01.941
raised our rates.

420
00:46:02.458 --> 00:46:03.742
Chuck went ballistic.

421
00:46:03.744 --> 00:46:05.945
He wanted to go to war.

422
00:46:05.947 --> 00:46:07.546
I drew a line.

423
00:46:08.005 --> 00:46:09.515
He wouldn't back down.

424
00:46:10.382 --> 00:46:11.759
So I forced him out.

425
00:46:16.958 --> 00:46:20.192
It never occurred to me
that I could hurt him.

426
00:46:21.018 --> 00:46:23.354
He always seemed so strong.

427
00:46:24.198 --> 00:46:25.731
But he wasn't.

428
00:46:27.441 --> 00:46:30.235
I think he did what he did because of me.

429
00:46:37.364 --> 00:46:41.198
Well. Howard. I guess
that's your cross to bear.

430
00:46:59.799 --> 00:47:02.799
Look at her go.

431
00:47:02.801 --> 00:47:05.403
So. I'm gonna make some coffee.

432
00:47:05.405 --> 00:47:07.481
Anybody want some?
